editorialSummary.text: Sleek, contemporary eatery offering global seafood dishes & a raw bar amid colorful nautical decor.

originalText.text:
Seawalk Restaurant and Lounge is a hidden gem located in the bustling neighborhood of Dyckman in New York City. This coastal-inspired restaurant and lounge has been making waves with its fresh, sustainable ingredients and exceptional dining experience, making it a strong contender for both a Michelin star and James Beard Award.

The restaurant's menu features a range of seafood dishes that are expertly prepared with a focus on quality and sustainability. From raw bar favorites like oysters and ceviche to entrees like grilled octopus and pan-seared scallops, Seawalk's menu showcases the best of what the ocean has to offer.

The restaurant's chic, modern interior provides the perfect backdrop for a memorable dining experience. The main dining room features sleek, contemporary design elements and large windows that flood the space with natural light, while the lounge area offers cozy seating and a relaxed ambiance for guests looking to unwind over drinks and small bites.

The cocktail menu at Seawalk is equally impressive, featuring a range of creative and refreshing drinks made with high-quality spirits and fresh ingredients. The lounge area is the perfect spot to enjoy a pre-dinner drink or a nightcap after a delicious meal.

With its commitment to sustainability, dedication to quality ingredients, and exceptional dining experience, Seawalk Restaurant and Lounge is a top contender for both a Michelin star and James Beard Award. Whether you're in the mood for an intimate dinner or a casual evening of drinks with friends, Seawalk is a must-visit destination in the heart of Dyckman.

originalText.text: This has to be the worst restaurant I have been all year. The restaurant itself seems clean and the decoration is nice. They open for dinner at 5 pm on Sunday and we arrive at 7:30. Our appetizers arrived one hour later, when we told the waiter why is it taking so long, he reply "because it being made fresh". It's fried food and sea food, that does not take that long. The restaurant also has a B rating and it's was empty through our dining time there. The sangria did not even taste like it was made with wine and the service sucked as well. I will definitely not be dining here again. The fish is not worth the price nor were the appetizers. I give this a 1 star because of the decor, everything else was bad. #bad #dontdinehere #1star #badservice #stayaway
